rinse /rɪns/

(rinsing,rinsed,rinses) 

1. V-T When you rinse something, you wash it in clean water in order to remove dirt or soap from it. 冲洗 

例： It's important to rinse the rice to remove the starch. 淘洗大米去掉淀粉很重要。 

2. N-COUNT Rinse is also a noun. 冲洗 

例： Clean skin means plenty of lather followed by a rinse with water. 清洁的皮肤意味着用大量的皂沫清洗，然后用水冲洗。 

3. V-T If you rinse your mouth, you wash it by filling your mouth with water or with a liquid that kills germs, then spitting it out. 漱 (口) 

例： Use a toothbrush on your tongue as well, and rinse your mouth frequently. 用牙刷在舌头上也刷刷，然后频频漱口。 

4. PHRASAL VERB Rinse out means the same as . 漱 (口) 

例： After her meal she invariably rinsed out her mouth. 饭后她总漱口。 

5. N-MASS Rinse is also a noun. 漱口液 

例： ...mouth rinses with fluoride. …有氟化物的漱口液。

